Ogun State governor, Dapo Abiodun, at his swearing-in ceremony, promised to improve the standard of education in the state and on Friday, the governor has suspended with immediate effect payment of N3 700 as PTA fee inherited by the past administration. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1258532" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=300%2C200&#038;ssl=1" alt="Abiodun " width="300" height="200" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=1024%2C682&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?resize=560%2C373&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/IMG_20190921_080255.jpg?w=1920&amp;ssl=1 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> At the Abeot forum for stakeholders in the education sector of the state, Gov Abiodun, noted that the suspension of the payment “rumoured to have been approved by me,” is to unburden parents and guardian. He also asked officials to workout plans to ensure insurance and accessories, which the N3,700 was meant for is covered. On his Twitter page, Dapo Abiodun wrote: “I have suspended with immediate effect, the N3,700 PTA fee inherited from the immediate past administration but rumoured to have been approved by me, to be paid by parents and guardians of students in our State-owned primary and secondary schools. “I disclosed this in Abeoat the Forum held with stakeholders in our education sector today. I have mandated concerned officials to look at how we can make insurance & accessories, which were part of the details of the fee, work without making our parents & guardians uncomfortable. “Our administration promised to offer free education at these levels, and as our performance has so far shown, we will not renege. “In addition to this show of faith, we have, amongst other things, begun rehabilitation of 236 primary and secondary schools in the State and we will focus on teacher training to develop the pro fession and sector. #BuildingOurFutureTogether,” Abiodun said.  Vanguard As he approves promotion for over 10,000 teachers The Academic Staff Union of Secondary Schools, ASUSS, Ogun State Chapter has applauded the state Governor, Prince Dapo Abiodun, the Deputy, Engr. Noimat Salako and the Chief of Staff Alhaji Shuaib Salisu for writing right the wrongdoing of the immediate past administration… September 7, 2019 In "Education" Gov. Dapo Abiodun of Ogun on Saturday appointed Mr Olatokunbo Talabi as the Secretary to the State Government (SSG). June 15, 2019 In "News" Arepo Central Community Development Association, (ACCDA) an umbrella development group comprising no fewer than twenty estates and communities in Arepo, has congratulated the new Governor of Ogun state His Excellency, Prince Dapo Abiodun and his deputy Engr. Mrs. Noimot Salako-Oyedele as they assumed the mantle of leadership of the Gateway… June 5, 2019 In "Metro"